            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Education was good earlier but year on year basis it worst.\nSchool management is money minded.\nThey increased fee this year around 20%.\nThey got CBSE affiliation around 2-3 year back. They are not following book standard as per ncert.\nEvery couple of year they changed either books publication/vender reason for this everyone knows.\n\nThe books are very expensive they forced to take stationary as well even last year notebook n stationery already have.\nThis year books cost Rs 8700+\n\nThey are not following NCERT norms\nTransport fee is also hiked around 40%\nEarlier there was good space for play ground but during covid they constructed college behind the school by reducing the ground to half.",
